did.unittitle: Gelman Library, Slavic, East European, and Asian Reading Room records
did.abstract: This collection contains correspondence, foundation proposals, grants, conference reports, articles and papers, research fellows, exchange participants, research assistants. The material relates to the workings of the Reading Room. This material dates from 1962-95.

prefercite.head: Preferred citation
prefercite.p: Gelman Library, Slavic, East European, and Asian Reading Room records, Special Collections Research Center, The George Washington University.

accessrestrict.head: Restrictions on Access
accessrestrict.p: Series 1 is closed to research for 50 years from date of record creation.

userestrict.head: Restrictions on Use
userestrict.p: Some material may be copyrighted or restricted. It is the patron's obligation to determine and satisfy copyright or other case restrictions when publishing or otherwise distributing materials found in the collections.

bioghist.head: Historical or Biographical Note
bioghist.p: The Slavic, East European, and Asian Reading Room is a reference and research collection focusing primarily on the post World War II political, economic, and military affairs of the Russian Federation, Ukraine, the Czech Republic, Slovakia, China, Taiwan, Japan, and Korea. It was formerly known as the Sino-Soviet Information Center.

scopecontent.head: Collection Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: This collection contains correspondence, foundation proposals, grants, conference reports, articles and papers, research fellows, exchange participants, research assistants. The material relates to the workings of the Reading Room. This material dates from 1962-95.

arrangement.head: Collection Organization
arrangement.p: Organized into two series both titled Office files.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series contains Sino-Soviet Center files. These materials date from 1980-89 and cover such topics as the Soviet Interview Project, Harvard project materials, correspondence, films, general survey codebook.
This series has a container list in electronic form, please ask staff for assistance.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series contains foundation proposals, grants, conference reports, articles and papers, correspondence, research fellows, exchange participants, research assistants, SDS attack on the Institute (1969), WTOP radio programs hosted by Kurt London (director). This material dates from 1962-95.
